**JSON File**

```json
[
  {
    "name": "Banggai Islands",
    "full_address": "Banggai Islands, Central Sulawesi, Indonesia",
    "order": 1
  },
  {
    "name": "Raja Ampat",
    "full_address": "Raja Ampat, West Papua, Indonesia",
    "order": 2
  },
  {
    "name": "Togean Islands",
    "full_address": "Togean Islands, Central Sulawesi, Indonesia",
    "order": 3
  },
  {
    "name": "Bali",
    "full_address": "Bali, Indonesia",
    "order": 4
  },
  {
    "name": "Sulawesi",
    "full_address": "Sulawesi, Indonesia",
    "order": 5
  },
  {
    "name": "Nusa Lembongan",
    "full_address": "Nusa Lembongan, Bali, Indonesia",
    "order": 6
  }
]
```

**Explanation**

The name of each location was extracted from the caption using the `.text` attribute. The full address was extracted by combining the name of the location with the name of the region or province in which it is located. The order of each location was extracted by counting the number of times the location was mentioned in the caption.

For example, the name of the first location is "Banggai Islands". The full address is "Banggai Islands, Central Sulawesi, Indonesia". The order is 1, because the location is mentioned first in the caption.

The same process was applied to all six locations. The resulting JSON file contains a list of objects, each of which contains the name, full address, and order of a location.

